}}'''Driver Reifen und KFZ-Technik''' is a German company  providing tire and car services. Since 1994, the company has been part of the Italian tire manufacturer [[Pirelli]] and is a 100% subsidiary of ''Deutsche Pirelli Reifen Holding GmbH''. The company has more than 80 stores in Germany operating under several brand names including ''Pneumobil, Driver,'' and ''Reifen-Wagner''. It employs approximately 500 people and had revenues of approx. €100 million in 2016.<ref>{{citation/core|Surname1=Echo Zeitungen GmbH|Title=Pneumobil kauft zu|language=German|URL=http://www.echo-online.de/wirtschaft/wirtschaft-suedhessen/pneumobil-kauft-zu_17976272.htm|AccessDate=2017-09-27
}}</ref> The company’s service offering includes tires, rims, high-quality car services and car accessories for almost all types of vehicles. The company is headquartered in Breuberg in the Odenwald region, on the factory premises of Pirelli Deutschland GmbH.

== History ==
The company was established in 1979 and acquired by the Pirelli Group in 1994. After taking over, among others, the branches of Reifen Laupichler in the metropolitan area of Hamburg and Hanover the company, then named Pneumobil GmbH, acquired the tire retailers Junginger of Metzingen and Reifen Herl of [[Nürtingen]] with a total of 15 stores on 1 November 2003.<ref>{{citation/core|Periodical=Reifenpresse|Title=Jetzt auch offiziell: Herl und Junginger zu Pneumobil|Date=2003-10-31|language=German|URL=http://reifenpresse.de/2003/10/31/jetzt-auch-offiziell-herl-und-junginger-zu-pneumobil/|AccessDate=2017-09-27
}}</ref>

Effective 1 January 2012, Christian F. Mühlhäuser took the helm of Pneumobil succeeding Hans-Ulrich Röske who had gone into early retirement after working more than 40 years for Pirelli Deutschland.<ref>{{citation/core|Surname1=Vogel Business Media GmbH & Co. KG|Title=Pneumobil hat neuen Geschäftsführer|language=German|URL=http://www.kfz-betrieb.vogel.de/pneumobil-hat-neuen-geschaeftsfuehrer-a-346887/|AccessDate=2017-09-27
}}</ref><ref>{{citation/core|Periodical=Reifenpresse|Title=Christian Mühlhäuser neuer Pneumobil-Geschäftsführer|Date=2012-01-30|language=German|URL=http://www.reifenpresse.de/2012/01/30/christian-muehlhaeuser-neuer-pneumobil-geschaeftsfuehrer/|AccessDate=2017-09-27
}}</ref> Mühlhäuser joined Pirelli as a working student in 1993. Later, after studying engineering and obtaining an MBA degree at US universities, he assumed management functions in the areas of logistics and planning, quality and technology, and in Pirelli‘s headquarters in Milan. In 2009, he took the helm of the Pirelli motorcycle tire factory in Breuberg. 
[[File:Pneumobil_Niederlassung_Stuttgart-Weilimdorf.jpg|thumb|Pneumobil branch Stuttgart-Weilimdorf]]
Pneumobil went on to acquire more companies such as Reifen Blank of [[Düren]] on 1 August 2013 <ref>{{citation/core|Periodical=Reifenpresse|Title=Pneumobil weiter auf Einkaufstour|Date=2013-08-06|language=German|URL=http://reifenpresse.de/2013/08/06/pneumobil-weiter-auf-einkaufstour/|AccessDate=2017-09-27
}}</ref> and PneuCenter RRT GmbH of [[Sindelfingen]] on 1 September 2013.<ref>{{citation/core|Surname1=klautke|Periodical=Gummibereifung|Title=Pneumobil übernimmt PneuCenter in Sindelfingen|Date=2013-08-27|language=German|URL=http://gummibereifung.de/nachrichten/pneumobil-uebernimmt-pneucenter|AccessDate=2017-09-27
}}</ref> At the same time, Pneumobil obtained possession of Reifen-Wagner R.W. Auto-Technik, a [[Landshut]]-based company offering specialized tire retail and car services. The 100 employees of Reifen-Wagner were kept on the payroll and the service network with a total of ten workshops exclusively based in the state of Bavaria was also taken over.<ref>{{cite web|title=Pneumobil kauft Reifen Wagner - autohaus.de|periodical=|publisher=|url=http://www.autohaus.de/nachrichten/reifenhandel-kfz-service-pneumobil-kauft-reifen-wagner-1279454.html|deadurl=|accessdate=2017-09-27|archiveurl=|archivedate=|last=|date=|year=|month=|day=|language=German|pages=|quote=}}</ref><ref>{{citation/core|Surname1=Vogel Business Media GmbH & Co. KG|Title=Pneumobil schluckt Reifen-Wagner|language=German|URL=http://www.kfz-betrieb.vogel.de/pneumobil-schluckt-reifen-wagner-a-413779/|AccessDate=2017-09-27
}}</ref>

On 13 September 2013, Pneumobil opened its first ''Driver Center'' in [[Frankfurt]]. A combination of show room, design lounge, consultation room, sales and service area, these flagship stores are designed to turn “purchasing tires and car services into an experience.”<ref>{{citation/core|Periodical=Reifenpresse|Title=In Frankfurt errichtet Pirelli ein „Driver Center“|Date=2013-08-02|language=German|URL=http://reifenpresse.de/2013/08/02/in-frankfurt-errichtet-pirelli-ein-driver-center/|AccessDate=2017-09-27
}}</ref><ref>{{citation/core|Surname1=bva-lehmi|Periodical=Gummibereifung|Title=Driver-Konzept gestartet|Date=2013-09-09|language=German|URL=http://www.gummibereifung.de/branchenberichte/driver-konzept-gestartet|AccessDate=2017-09-27
}}</ref><ref>{{citation/core|Periodical=Reifenpresse|Title=Schon über 3.500 Kunden in Pirellis neuem Frankfurter „Driver Center“|Date=2013-12-13|language=German|URL=http://reifenpresse.de/2013/12/13/schon-ueber-3-500-kunden-in-pirellis-neuem-frankfurter-driver-center/|AccessDate=2017-09-27
}}</ref>  The layout of the store’s workshop area is inspired by the [[Pit stop|pit lanes]] in motor sports.<ref>{{citation/core|Periodical=Top Magazin Frankfurt|Title=Driver Center Frankfurt - Revolution Reifen & Service|Date=2013-12-12|language=German|URL=http://www.top-magazin-frankfurt.de/redaktion/business-finance/driver-center-frankfurt-revolution-reifen-service/|AccessDate=2017-09-27
}}</ref>  Effective 1 October 2013, Pneumobil acquired Reifen-Wagner I.S. Auto-Service GmbH & Co. KG, also based in Landshut, with its 15 stores and 140 employees.<ref>{{citation/core|Surname1=klautke|Periodical=Gummibereifung|Title=Pneumobil übernimmt nun auch Reifen-Wagner I.S. Auto-Service|Date=2013-09-11|language=German|URL=http://gummibereifung.de/nachrichten/pneumobil-uebernimmt-nun-auch-reifen|AccessDate=2017-09-27
}}</ref> September 2014 saw the opening of more Driver Centers in [[Bonn]], [[Aachen]], and [[Trier]].<ref>{{citation/core|Periodical=Reifenpresse|Title=Netzwerk der „Driver Center“ um drei Standorte erweitert|Date=2014-09-11|language=German|URL=http://www.reifenpresse.de/2014/09/11/netzwerk-der-driver-center-um-drei-standorte-erweitert/|AccessDate=2017-09-27
}}</ref>

On 7 April 2017, Pneumobil GmbH changed its name to Pneumobil Reifen und KFZ-Technik GmbH by registering the new name in trade register B of the local court of [[Darmstadt]]. Shortly afterwards, on 1 July 2017, the Cologne-based tire retailer Reifen Schäfer e.K. was taken over by Pneumobil.<ref>{{citation/core|Periodical=Reifenpresse|Title=Reifen Schäfer aus Köln geht an Pneumobil|Date=2017-06-19|language=German|URL=http://www.reifenpresse.de/2017/06/19/reifen-schaefer-aus-koeln-geht-an-pneumobil/|AccessDate=2017-09-27
}}</ref> 
[[File:Reifen-Wagner_Ingolstadt.jpg|thumb|Pneumobil branch Ingolstadt]]
After a redesign of six Pneumobil stores in the area of Frankfurt and two Reifen-Wagner stores in Munich, there are 21 Driver Centers (as of October 2017) which are all 100% property of Pneumobil Reifen und KFZ-Technik GmbH. In addition, there are other Driver Centers in the network of Pneumobil’s sister company ''Driver Handelssysteme GmbH'' which is also a subsidiary of ''Deutsche Pirelli Reifen Holding GmbH''. 

At the end of September 2017, the former Reifen Wagner branch in Hanauerstr. 42, Munich was reopened as the Driver Center Munich. The first European P-Zero World of the Pirelli Group was also formed within this Driver Center. Driver Reifen und KFZ-Technik GmbH have also been operating it since it opened.<ref>{{Citation|title=Driver Reifen und KFZ-Technik|date=2018-10-17|url=https://de.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Driver_Reifen_und_KFZ-Technik&oldid=181891627|work=Wikipedia|language=de|access-date=2018-11-09}}</ref> <ref>{{Citation|title=Driver Reifen und KFZ-Technik|date=2018-10-17|url=https://de.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Driver_Reifen_und_KFZ-Technik&oldid=181891627|work=Wikipedia|language=de|access-date=2018-11-09}}</ref> 

On 29 December 2017, ''Pneumobil Reifen und KFZ-Technik GmbH'' changed it name to ''Driver Reifen und KFZ-Technik GmbH'' with legal effect.<ref>{{Citation|title=Driver Reifen und KFZ-Technik|date=2018-10-17|url=https://de.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Driver_Reifen_und_KFZ-Technik&oldid=181891627|work=Wikipedia|language=de|access-date=2018-11-09}}</ref> Christian F. Mühlhäuser was the Managing Director until 22 January 2018.<ref>{{Citation|title=Driver Reifen und KFZ-Technik|date=2018-10-17|url=https://de.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Driver_Reifen_und_KFZ-Technik&oldid=181891627|work=Wikipedia|language=de|access-date=2018-11-09}}</ref> On 1 July 2018, it was announced that he would become the Managing Director of the world’s leading tire manufacturer, Bridgestone.<ref>{{Citation|title=Driver Reifen und KFZ-Technik|date=2018-10-17|url=https://de.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Driver_Reifen_und_KFZ-Technik&oldid=181891627|work=Wikipedia|language=de|access-date=2018-11-09}}</ref> On 16 March 2018, Thorsten Schäfer became the new Managing Director of Driver Reifen und KFZ-Technik GmbH.<ref>{{Citation|title=Driver Reifen und KFZ-Technik|date=2018-10-17|url=https://de.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Driver_Reifen_und_KFZ-Technik&oldid=181891627|work=Wikipedia|language=de|access-date=2018-11-09}}</ref> Since 1 August 2018, there have been two new locations in the Driver network: Haßloch and Landau in the Palatinate region. 

This brings the total number of branches in Germany to 78.[[File:Driver_Center_Frankfurt.jpg|thumb|Pneumobil branch Frankfurt/Main]]

== Stores and brands ==
The approx. 80 stores of Pneumobil Reifen und KFZ-Technik GmbH operate under three different brand names. The ''Pneumobil'' brand is predominantly used in the Rhine/Main/Ruhr metropolitan areas as well as Stuttgart, Hamburg, and Hanover. In Bavaria, the company mainly relies on the ''Reifen-Wagner'' brand with its almost century-long tradition. Since the opening of the Frankfurt Driver Center in September 2013 new outlets also carry the ''Driver''™ logo.

== Service Portfolio ==
The company‘s product portfolio includes tires of renowned manufacturers such as [[Pirelli]], [[Continental AG|Continental]], [[Dunlop Tyres|Dunlop]], [[Goodyear Tire and Rubber Company|Goodyear]], [[Kumho Tire|Kumho,]] [[Michelin]] and several others, [[Rim (wheel)|rims]], high-quality car services  and car accessories for almost all types of vehicles. The tire portfolio on offer ranges from special tires for container stackers in the [[Port of Hamburg]] to wheelbarrow tires and from Ultra High Performance tires to environmentally-friendly Eco tires. Besides services for private customers, the company also offers services for vehicle fleets and commercial vehicles used by businesses.

== Awards ==
Pneumobil has won several awards for the quality of its service. In 2010, 2011, 2013, 2015, and 2016 it ranked No. 1 in the “Tire Retailer Service Study” conducted by the German Institute for Service Quality (DISQ) on behalf of the German n-tv television network. The study sampled 14 tire retailers and tire retail chains with a minimum of 25 outlets across Germany with respect to both their consulting competency and product presentation.<ref>{{citation/core|Periodical=Reifenpresse|Title=Reifenhandel ist fachkundig, aber … – Pneumobil bei DISQ-Servicestudie vorn|Date=2016-09-09|language=German|URL=http://www.reifenpresse.de/2016/09/09/reifenhandel-ist-fachkundig-aber-pneumobil-bei-disq-servicestudie-vorn/|AccessDate=2017-09-27
}}</ref><ref>{{citation/core|Surname1=n-tv Nachrichtenfernsehen|Periodical=n-tv.de|Title=Die besten Reifenhändler|language=German|URL=http://www.n-tv.de/ratgeber/tests/Die-besten-Reifenhaendler-article17905411.html|AccessDate=2017-09-27
}}</ref><ref>{{citation/core|Periodical=Automotive-Aktuell.de|Title=PNEUMOBIL GMBH ERZIELT ERNEUT SPITZENERGEBNIS - Automotive-Aktuell.de|Date=2015-08-14|language=German|URL=https://www.automotive-aktuell.de/pneumobil-gmbh-erzielt-erneut-spitzenergebnis-23431.html|AccessDate=2017-09-27
}}</ref><ref>{{citation/core|Surname1=n-tv Nachrichtenfernsehen|Periodical=n-tv.de|Title=Die besten Reifenhändler|language=German|URL=http://www.n-tv.de/ratgeber/tests/Die-besten-Reifenhaendler-article14480131.html|AccessDate=2017-09-27
}}</ref>

In 2016, Pneumobil won the study “Tire and Car Service Atlas” conducted by the [[Cologne]]-based Service Value GmbH for the third time in a row.<ref>{{cite web|title=ServiceAtlas Reifen- und Kfz-Service 2016|periodical=|publisher=|url=http://www.servicevalue.de/studien-tests/themenschwerpunkte/autoservice/studie/serviceatlas-reifen-und-kfz-service-2016/|deadurl=|format=|accessdate=2017-09-27|archiveurl=|archivedate=|last=|date=|year=|month=|day=|language=German|pages=|quote=}}</ref> The results of the study are based on 1,300 customer ratings for a set of 30 general and industry-specific service and performance criteria.

In February 2017, the DISQ held an awards ceremony at the Berlin representation of Bertelsmann during which it presented Pneumobil with the 2017 German Service Award in the category “Travel and Mobility - On Site Consultancy” in recognition of its customer friendliness.<ref>{{citation/core|Surname1=bva-lehmi|Periodical=Gummibereifung|Title=Pneumobil erhält DISQ-Urteil "sehr gut"|Date=2017-02-16|language=German|URL=http://www.gummibereifung.de/nachrichten/pneumobil-erhaelt-disq-urteil-sehr-gut|AccessDate=2017-09-27
}}</ref> The series of awards also continues under the new name of Driver Reifen und KFZ-Technik GmbH. In September 2018, first place was once again taken by the “Tire Retailer Service Study” of the German Institute for Service Quality (DISQ).<ref>{{Citation|title=Driver Reifen und KFZ-Technik|date=2018-10-17|url=https://de.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Driver_Reifen_und_KFZ-Technik&oldid=181891627|work=Wikipedia|language=de|access-date=2018-11-09}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|title=Driver Reifen und KFZ-Technik|date=2018-10-17|url=https://de.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Driver_Reifen_und_KFZ-Technik&oldid=181891627|work=Wikipedia|language=de|access-date=2018-11-09}}</ref> In October 2018, the company once again achieved overall victory in the Tire and Car Service Atlas 2018.<ref>{{Citation|title=Driver Reifen und KFZ-Technik|date=2018-10-17|url=https://de.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Driver_Reifen_und_KFZ-Technik&oldid=181891627|work=Wikipedia|language=de|access-date=2018-11-09}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|title=Driver Reifen und KFZ-Technik|date=2018-10-17|url=https://de.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Driver_Reifen_und_KFZ-Technik&oldid=181891627|work=Wikipedia|language=de|access-date=2018-11-09}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|title=Driver Reifen und KFZ-Technik|date=2018-10-17|url=https://de.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Driver_Reifen_und_KFZ-Technik&oldid=181891627|work=Wikipedia|language=de|access-date=2018-11-09}}</ref>

== Vocational Training and Environmental Commitment ==

Driver offers vocational training for retailers and car technicians and provides a cooperative degree program for high-school students wishing to become automobile dealers.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ausbildung|periodical=|publisher=|url=https://www.pneumobil.info/karriere/ausbildung.html|deadurl=|accessdate=2017-09-27|archiveurl=|archivedate=|last=|date=|year=|month=|day=|language=German|pages=|quote=}}</ref> Driver’s commitment to the environment is based on streamlined logistics processes, efficient use of materials and advanced energy concepts. In addition, the company has commissioned its disposal and recycling processes to selected and certified specialist companies.

