'''Magnus Mandersson''' (born May 12, 1959) is a [[Sweden|Swedish]] businessman. He was Executive [[Vice President]]<ref name = "EVP">[http://www.ericsson.com/thecompany/press/releases/2011/10/1558978 Magnus Mandersson appointed Executive Vice President of Ericsson]. 2011-10-28. Retrieved on 2011-10-28.</ref> at [[telecommunications]] company [[Ericsson]]<ref name = "EricssonMan">[http://www.ericsson.com/thecompany/corporate_governance/company_management/magnus_mandersson Magnus Mandersson - Ericsson]. 2010-11-02. Retrieved on 2011-02-13.</ref> from 2011 to 2017<ref name = "LeavingEric">[https://www.ericsson.com/en/press-releases/2017/11/ericsson-announces-changes-to-executive-team Ericsson announces changes to Executive Team]. 2017-11-07. Retrieved on 2017-11-23.</ref>, and is currently chairman of [[Ericsson Broadcast and Media Services|Red Bee Media]].<ref name = "RBM">[http://www.ericsson.com/broadcastandmedia/who-we-are/ Who We Are - Broadcast and Media]. Retrieved on 2017-11-23.</ref>

== Biography ==

Magnus currently serves as the chairman of [[Ericsson Broadcast and Media Services|Red Bee Media]], a British broadcasting and media services company originally part of the [[BBC]]. He is also a member of the University Board of [[Lund University]]<ref name = "LU">[http://www.lunduniversity.lu.se/about/management-leadership/university-board Lund University - University Board]. 2017-11-03. Retrieved on 2017-11-23.</ref> and the Supervisory Council of [[Interogo Foundation]].<ref name = "Interogo">[https://www.interogoholding.com/governance/interogo-foundation/ Governance of Interogo Foundation]. Retrieved on 2017-11-23.</ref>

At Ericsson, his last role was as head of [[Ericsson#Business_Unit_Global_Services|Business Unit Global Services]]. Prior to assuming this role in 2010, he had been responsible for Business Unit CDMA Mobile Systems, Ericsson's businesses in Northern Europe, the Global Customer Account [[Deutsche Telekom AG]] and  Managed Services business globally.<ref name = "EricssonMan"/>

Preceding his work at Ericsson, he has held management positions within the Swedish conglomerate [[Kinnevik]], as both [[Chief operating officer|COO]] of [[Millicom]] SA and [[Chief executive officer|CEO]] of [[Tele2]] Europe. <ref name = "Kinnevik">[http://www.kinnevik.se/Documents/Pdf/AnnualReports/sv/Arsredovisning_1997.pdf?epslanguage=sv Kinnevik Annual Report]. 1997. Retrieved on 2009-06-25.</ref> Mandersson also held the position as the first President of Comviq [[Vietnam]]/[[Mobifone]] in 1994. In the beginning of his career, he worked at [[IKEA]] in Europe and Asia. <ref name="BMag">[http://www.backbonemag.com/Press_Release/Items/press_release_01181001.asp Backbone Magazine - New heads of business units Global Services and CDMA appointed] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110707203654/http://www.backbonemag.com/Press_Release/Items/press_release_01181001.asp |date=2011-07-07 }}. 2010-01-18. Retrieved on 2011-02-13.</ref>

Mandersson holds a [[Bachelor's degree]] in [[Business Administration]] from [[Lund University]]. He has been residing, with his family, in [[Luxembourg]] since 1997.{{Citation needed|date=November 2009}}

