'''Thierry Jacquillat''' (July 29, 1938 in [[Versailles (city)|Versailles]], [[France]] &ndash; January 2010<ref>[http://www.boursier.com/vals/FR/pernod-ricard-deces-de-l-ancien-dirigeant-thierry-jacquillat-news-366072.htm Pernod-Ricard: dècès de l'ancien dirigeant Thierry Jacquillat], Boursier.com 2010-01-13 {{fr icon}}</ref>) was president of [[Paris-ile de France Capitale Economique]] and former number 2 of [[Pernod Ricard]]. He started to work for the [[Pernod Fils]] company at the age of 25, and was secretary-general of the company at the time of its merger with the [[Ricard Group]] in 1974. The merger was led by Jacquillat, who then held the position of Director General at Pernod Ricard until 2000.<ref>[http://www.katagogi.com/Profile/Profile.aspx?l=EN&fid=17364&No=e5e0f29e-0ee5-4380-805b-25323432212a&PreveVal=11882|1EqP7mB2w0IT3LmaA5flJmhw5ZrN9MzE3VBztD2K99I=|6uadx1WAqgWiF2UlEVTWHQ==1 Katalogi.com: Thierry Jacquillat], accessed 2010-09-09</ref> “In his almost 40 years with Pernod Ricard, Thierry Jacquillat helped transform a French family-run business with 1,100 employees into one of the top world leaders in [[wine]]s and spirits, with nearly 15,000 employees and a presence in nearly 100 countries”

